- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and specifically preposition sense disambiguation. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper uses clustering and vector operations to disambiguate preposition senses. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with semantic information and learning sense-specific preposition representations. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible category as the paper deals with extracting features from a large corpus of text. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper may use neural network models for preposition sense disambiguation.
